<br>
I read a story awhile back about a boy scout up in Ohio who tried to build his own reactor.  All he succeded in doing was creating a bunch of mostly useless radioactive material.  Still, the fact that he managed to extract dangerous quantities of thorium and uranium from consumer product raises the possibility that his feat could be replicated by terrorists to create, at the very least, a nasty little dirty bomb.<br>
<br>
This is one of the reasons that I'd like to go to space.  Wackos usually are too ignorant to be able to extend their reach out that far.  I don't want to give anyone the impression that fear is my main motivation for being a space nut, it isn't.  There are half a dozon factors that are more important to me.<br>
